event.title: found within its boundaries, including Lake Abert, Summer

data.event: The county is named for the many lakes found within its boundaries, including Lake Abert, Summer Lake, Hart Lake, and Goose Lake.

event.title: is generally divided between the communities around Lakeview and Paisley to the south and the communities around Christmas

data.event: The county is generally divided between the communities around Lakeview and Paisley to the south and the communities around Christmas Valley, Fort Rock, and Silver Lake to the north.
Although lumber was once a primary economic driver in Lake County, today only one mill remains, at Lakeview.

event.title: found in the Paisley Caves in northern Lake County in 2007

data.event: Pre-Clovis era coprolites found in the Paisley Caves in northern Lake County in 2007 have been radiocarbon dated to 14,300 calendar years before present.

event.title: found prehistoric artifacts in the Fort Rock Caves of northern Lake County in 1938

data.event: Luther Cressman found prehistoric artifacts in the Fort Rock Caves of northern Lake County in 1938, including basketry, stone tools, and a cache of woven sagebrush bark sandals which have been dated to more than 10,000 years ago.
